8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 527, L.D. 1297, “Resolve, to Establish
10 the Committee to Study the Use of Sunflower Crops to Produce Biofuels”
11 Amend the resolve by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'Resolve, to Establish the Committee to Study the Use of Sunflower Crops to Produce
13 Biofuels and Other Products'
14 Amend the resolve by inserting after the title the following:
15 'Emergency preamble. Whereas, acts and resolves of the Legislature do not
16 become effective until 90 days after adjournment unless enacted as emergencies; and
17 Whereas, the Legislature finds it is important to explore the feasibility of new
18 opportunities for agricultural producers in Maine, to enhance on-farm efficiencies and to
19 expand new markets while contributing to the growth of rural economies in Maine; and
20 Whereas, this legislation establishes the Committee to Study the Use of Sunflower
21 Crops to Produce Biofuels and Other Products; and
22 Whereas, this legislation needs to take effect before the expiration of the 90-day
23 period to allow the Committee to Study the Use of Sunflower Crops to Produce Biofuels
24 and Other Products to conduct its work as soon as possible so that it may report back to the
25 Legislature by December 3, 2025; and
26 Whereas, in the judgment of the Legislature, these facts create an emergency within
27 the meaning of the Constitution of Maine and require the following legislation as
28 immediately necessary for the preservation of the public peace, health and safety; now,
29 therefore, be it'
30 Amend the resolve in section 1 in the 2nd line (page 1, line 2 in L.D.) by inserting after
31 the following: "Biofuels" the following: 'and Other Products'
32 Amend the resolve by striking out all of section 2 (page 1, lines 4 to 27 in L.D.) and
33 inserting the following:
Page 1 - 132LR1642(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 527, L.D. 1297
1 'Sec. 2. Committee membership. Resolved: That, notwithstanding Joint Rule
2 353, the committee consists of 9 members appointed as follows:
3 1. Two members of the Senate, appointed by the President of the Senate, including a
4 member from each of the 2 parties holding the largest number of seats in the Legislature,
5 one member who serves on the Joint Standing Committee on Energy, Utilities and
6 Technology and one member who represents Aroostook County;
7 2. Two members of the House of Representatives, appointed by the Speaker of the
8 House, one member who serves on the Joint Standing Committee on Agriculture,
9 Conservation and Forestry and one member who represents Aroostook County;
10 3. One member who serves on the Maine Potato Board, appointed by the President of
11 the Senate;
12 4. One member representing the Maine Energy Marketers Association, appointed by
13 the President of the Senate;
14 5. One member representing the University of Maine at Presque Isle, appointed by the
15 Speaker of the House; and
16 6. Two members representing renewable energy companies in the State, appointed by
17 the Speaker of the House.'
18 Amend the resolve in section 5 in the 2nd line (page 1, line 39 in L.D.) by inserting
19 after the following: "biofuels" the following: ', food-grade oil and livestock feed'
20 Amend the resolve by adding before the summary the following:
21 'Emergency clause. In view of the emergency cited in the preamble, this legislation
22 takes effect when approved.'
23 Amend the resolve by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
24 section number to read consecutively.
25 SUMMARY
2266 This amendment renames the study committee established in the resolve the
2277 Committee to Study the Use of Sunflower Crops to Produce Biofuels and Other Products.
2288 The amendment revises the membership of the committee. The amendment directs the
2299 committee to study the feasibility of using the State's sunflower crops to produce food-
3300 grade oil and livestock feed in addition to biofuels as proposed in the resolve. The
3311 amendment adds an emergency preamble and emergency clause to the resolve.
